**Fixing regex detection**

I'm realizing that the regex `/任务拆解\b/` isn’t correctly detecting Chinese headings due to the boundaries defined by `\b`, as Chinese characters are considered nonword. So, my function hasTaskSection won't catch these headings. I need a fix for this! A good solution could involve using `(?:\\s|$)` to avoid needing a strict boundary. The new patch will look like this: `/(?:^|\n)\s*#{1,6}\s*(?:任务拆解|任务计划|任务列表|开发任务|实施计划)(?:\s|$)/i`. Let's implement that!
